    {
      "id": "75333edc_449e11d3",
      "file_path": "examples/examples-onap-vcpe/src/main/resources/examples/config/ONAPvCPEStandalone/ApexConfig.json",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 40,
      "message": "This file is an example configuration for the apex-pdp running in the real ONAP environment so \"localhost\" would not be correct here. The correct value is the IP address or host name for DMaaP.\n\nThe user must change this file to suit their own installation and then this configuration is packaged into the TOSCA policy. Once the apex-pdp unpacks the TOSCA, it loads the policy and connects to whatever host name is in the configuration file.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2020-01-08 10:22:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "c592bc45_48974111",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5c5d75fb_b6b547e9",
      "file_path": "examples/examples-onap-vcpe/src/main/resources/logic/standalone/CheckVServerIdTask.js",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 31,
      "message": "In this example, I want to show chaining of states. OK, the example is a bit lame but it's hopefully easy to understand.\n\nThe first state checks the service ID blacklist, the next state checks the VServer ID blacklist and the final one checks the VNF ID blacklist. The policy then consists of a directed graph of three checking states and then a fourth state that decides what to do.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2020-01-08 10:22:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9931e9b9_13ef3322",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "c31c0466_c16f3b71",
      "file_path": "examples/examples-onap-vcpe/src/main/resources/logic/standalone/ControllerResponseTask.js",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 75,
      "message": "It's set at line 38.\n\nThe return value should be true except for cases where there is a real incompatibility type error in the policy. The case at line 85-86 where the VNF ID is not found should not happen (We should never get to here if the VNF ID is not in the context map), so that's an error in policy execution.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2020-01-08 10:22:55.000000000",
